Domain: Industry 4.0
Context: I am an automatic compliance monitoring system that receives data packets in JSON format from other AI systems regarding the security status of global incidents.
 


Evaluate the following keys:

    "TypeOfRegulation": "Data Protection and AI Governance",
    "DescriptionOfRegulation": "The EU AI Act regulates high-risk AI systems, including those in robotics and supply chains, requiring transparency, risk assessments, and human oversight to ensure safety and fundamental rights.",
    "ImpactOfRegulation": "Increases compliance costs for AI-integrated robotics, mandates detailed documentation and risk management, potentially delaying innovation but enhancing data security and ethical standards.",
    "ConsequencesOfRegulation": "For EU-based manufacturers, it may complicate partnerships with non-EU countries like India or China due to data transfer restrictions; export to USA/Canada could require dual compliance, risking delays in assembly and increased costs, potentially affecting competitiveness.",
    "ClassificationScoreOfRegulation": 3,
    "OtherInformation": "Emphasizes cybersecurity in supply chains; non-compliance risks fines up to 7% of global turnover, impacting cross-border collaborations.",
    "SourceOfEvidence": "https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/european-approach-artificial-intelligence, https://www.europarl.europa.eu/RegData/etudes/STUD/2020/634406/IPOL_STU(2020)634406_EN.pdf",
    "Sourcing": "3",
    "LLM_Name": "Grok",
    "LLM_Version": "4",
    "OnlineResearchTimestamp": "2025-10-23T12:00:00Z",
    "LearningTimeStamp": "",
    "AnswerTimeStamp": "2025-10-23T12:00:00Z",
    "QueryTimeStamp"
 
TypeOfRegulation
DescriptionOfRegulation
ImpactOfRegulation
ConsequencesOfRegulation
OtherInformation
LLM_Name
LLM_Version

 
Below, you will receive several JSON packets from the domain = SAP that contain these keys. Create a single new JSON structure using the following template. 

Template:
{
  "Domain": "<derived from SystemType, e.g. 'Industry 4.0', 'SAP', 'It Security', ...>",
  "Countries": [
    {
      "AnalyzedCountry":"<one of the Attributes AnalyzedCountry in the list of data>"
      "ClassificationScoreOfRegulation": "<median of ClassificationScoreOfRegulation values from input packets, range 1 to 10>",
      "Commonalities": [
        {
          "Key": "<one of: TypeOfRegulation, DescriptionOfRegulation, ImpactOfRegulation, ConsequencesOfRegulation,  OtherInformation, LLM_Name, LLM_Version>",
          "Value": "<consolidated statement representing common themes across all input packets for this key>"
        }
      ],
      "Deviations": [
        {
          "Key": "<one of: TypeOfRegulation, DescriptionOfRegulation, ImpactOfRegulation, ConsequencesOfRegulation,  OtherInformation, LLM_Name, LLM_Version>",
          "Deviations": [
            {
              "Source": "<Packet number or identifier, e.g., ‘Packet 1’>",
              "Text": "<specific deviation text unique to this packet>",
              "Significance": "<‘high’ for critical security risks, ‘medium’ for additional context/tools, ‘low’ for implied or less critical additions>"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "LLM_Name": "<your own llm-identifier>",
  "LLM_Version": "<your own llm-version>",
  "QueryTimeStamp": "<median of QueryTimeStamp values from input packets>",
  "AnswerTimeStamp": "<median of AnswerTimeStamp values from input packets>",
  "ProcessingTimeStamp": "<current timestamp in ISO format, e.g., ‘2025-10-03T15:15:00+02:00’>"
}

Query: 
Read all values and calculate a “median” from all values = statements. Put the commonalities at the beginning, evaluate the deviations in terms of their significance, and list them behind them. Explain all deviations of all datasets. In case no deviations of a dataset can be found, show the empty bracket [] as well. Don't supervise the existing results by your own insights. Don't optimize deviation results. Do the analysis separately per each AnalyzedCountry-attribute.


